THE police operation, Operation Restore, had a good outcome in Mfuleni, Cape Town on Friday, 24 February. This after cops searched a premises in Wydgelee Crescent, Wesbank and found crystal meth and mandrax tablets as well as an undisclosed amount of cash. A 47-year-old man was arrested on a charge of dealing in drugs and will appear in the Blue Downs Magistrates Court on Monday, 27 February. But that's not all. ALSO READ: Man bust for raping girl (8) Members of the Maitland Flying Squad also arrested a 56-year-old man in Gugulethu on Saturday, 25 February for possession of an imitation firearm and ammunition. The members followed up on information of firearms at the premises, searched it and found the imitation firearm with 11 rounds of ammunition, which were confiscated. They also searched a premises in Samora Machel, where they found three unlicensed firearms with 28 rounds of ammunition. REGISTER TO COMMENT Three men aged between 34 and 37 were arrested for possession of unlicensed firearms and ammunition. They will appear in the Athlone Magistrates Court soon.